<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 06 at 5:40PM MDT  by NWS Glasgow</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of west central Valley
County through 630 PM MDT...
At 540 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Hinsdale, or 23 miles west of Glasgow, moving north at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Hinsdale.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM MDT for
northeastern Montana.</instruction>
